(ii)   Wages shall be paid by the Employers at the work location, before
                                  quitting time, in cash or by cheque, payable at par in the locality of
                                  the work location. Accompanying each payment of wages shall be
                                  a statement, in writing, or email or epost, which can be retained by
                                  the employee, setting forth:

(a)     the period of time or the work for which the wages are
                                          being paid;

(b)     the rate of wages to which the employee is entitled;

(c)     the amount of wages to which the employee is entitled;

(d)     the amount of each deduction from the wages of the
                                          employee and the purpose for which each deduction is
                                          made;
